Mozambique's Defense and Security Forces (FDS) had killed a total of 37 terrorists and seized 21 weapons last week in Macomia district in the northern province of Cabo Delgado, according to a report by the national radio station Radio Mozambique on Saturday.
The report quoted the Commander-General of the Police of the Republic of Mozambique Bernardino Rafael, who was speaking to the 7th battalion of the FDS positioned in Macomia, one of the most affected zones by terrorist activities in the province, on Friday. 



